<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" CalDefCategory="HMI" Description="GIS-643 - Low radio Component Diagnostic Specification for Global A">
  <CalDefFileVersion>11</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>19MAY15</Date>
    <Description>First release for GIS-643 v1.1</Description>
    <Author>Sanghyun Ryu</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>21AUG2015</Date>
    <Description>re-release for GIS 643 v1.1 due to the CalID duplication</Description>
    <Author>Sanghyun Ryu</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>20150902</Date>
    <Description>Delete FTBs in ANC mic</Description>
    <Author>Sanghyun  Ryu</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>02SEP15</Date>
    <Description>Added B0010 / B124B / B1265</Description>
    <Author>Sanghyun Ryu</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>2/26/2016</Date>
    <Description>Per email agreement/review with Sanghyun Ryu on 3/3/2016, made the following updates: Deleted the DEBOUNCE_TIME CAL (CalID: _sVfOkJjTEeOY6q-k73fxZA) that was incorrected defined as a Boolean type CAL in the previous version of this caldef file, and replacing with a new DEBOUNCE_TIME CAL (CalID: _HKpgcN5hEeW58O1OdVks4w) correctly defined as an Integer. The same correction needed to be made within the GIS-621.caldef file to redefine the CAL Type of the DEBOUNCE_TIME CAL. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>3/2/2016</Date>
    <Description> Per email agreement/review with Sanghyun Ryu on 3/3/2016, made the following updates: Deleted all DTC_MASK Calibrations for the SWITCHED 14V (REMOTE ENABLE CIRCUIT) DTC (DTC_MASK_B1265_01, DTC_MASK_B1265_02, and DTC_MASK_B1265_04) since the SWITCHED 14V (REMOTE ENABLE CIRCUIT) DTC has been deleted to align with GIS-643 v1.4. Also updated the default values from False to True for all the DTC_MASK calibrations in this caldef file to help reduce CAL override proliferation.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>2015/05/25</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS643_DiagnosticCalDefGlobalA.caldef made the following updates: Specification version 1.5: DTC_MASK_B101D_31, DTC_MASK_B101D_34, DTC_MASK_B101D_35, DTC_MASK_B101D_36, DTC_MASK_B101D_39, DTC_MASK_B101D_3B, DTC_MASK_B101D_3C, DTC_MASK_B101E_46, DTC_MASK_B101E_47, DTC_MASK_B395A_08,  DTC_MASK_B395A_72, DTC_MASK_B1265_01, DTC_MASK_B1265_02,  and DTC_MASK_B1265_04. Also, the default values for the  VN_ACTIVATION and  RECOVERY_UNDER_OVER_VOLTAGE, and deleted the MANUFACTURER_ENABLE_COUNTER calibration that was confirmed not to be needed. </Description>
    <Author>Sanghyun Ryu</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>2016/12/08</Date>
    <Description>Within GIS643_DiagnosticCalDef_GlobalA.caldef file, per RTC CR#: 1249208 for Spec revision for GIS-643 v1.6 added the following three new calibrations: 1.) DTC_MASK_B395A_3A, 2.) DTC_MASK_B127E_00, and 3.) B127E_06. </Description>
    <Author>Jihyung Lim</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>12/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#: 1508336, within the GIS643_DiagnosticCalDef_GlobalA.caldef file added one diagnostic enable mask calibration (DTC_MASK_U0020_00) that was missing which the CSM already had included in the CAL Database that the Low Radio also needed to have included in the CAL Database.</Description>
    <Author>Zachary Lemons</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="U0020_00_LOW SPEED_CAN COMMUNICATION_BUS_PERFORMANCE - Upon handler notification that Source Id 0xFF has failed. Source Id 0xFF is used for all signals that have not yet been associated to a source Id." Name="DTC_MASK_U0020_00" References="GIS-643" Usage="LOW,GLOBALA,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_TOgokO41EeeJ-4EGVvY9Kg</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>12/15/2017</Date>
      <Description>Initial release of this calibration</Description>
      <Author>Zachary Lemons</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>true</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="DTC_ENABLE_CRITERIA - The absence of required nodes shall be mapped to a &#x2018;Lost Communication with {physical ECU}&#x2019; Trouble Code. There shall be an additional adjustable debounce time for each DTC, which shall be 2.5 Times the Timout. If a time-out occurs, the corresponding U-code must be stored in the state &#x2018;current&#x2019; and failure debouncing shall begin. If required, back-up values might be used for missing signals. Within the error debounce time the supervising ECU must heal &#x2018;current&#x2019; failures if the corresponding signal appears again.  If healing is not successful within the debounce time, the failure transition to the state &#x2018;history&#x2019;." Name="DEBOUNCE_TIME" Usage="LOW,GLOBALA,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_HKpgcN5hEeW58O1OdVks4w</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>2/26/2016</Date>
      <Description>Deleted the DEBOUNCE_TIME CAL (CalID: _sVfOkJjTEeOY6q-k73fxZA) that was incorrected defined as a Boolean type CAL in the previous version of this caldef file, and replacing with a new DEBOUNCE_TIME CAL (CalID: _HKpgcN5hEeW58O1OdVks4w) correctly defined as an Integer. </Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Integer>
      <Value>2500</Value>
      <MinValue>0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>10000</MaxValue>
      <Units>milliseconds</Units>
      <Resolution>1.0</Resolution>
    </Integer>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="DTC Enable Criteria.  It is important that the test enable criteria exclude power modes where the Low radio MODULE is not supposed to be fully functional.  If a DTC is enabled in Crank Request this has to be motivated and clearly shown that no false (ghost) codes will be set. For DTC&#x2019;s enabled in Off and Accessory power mode, they shall be linked with a secondary parameter (i.e. system voltage range) that clearly inhibit setting false (ghost) codes in under-voltage conditions" Name="DTC_CRANK_DELAY_TIME" Usage="LOW,GLOBALA,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_NvWtEEfTEeW-6Omy13RgGA</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>5/19/15</Date>
      <Description>Initial Release</Description>
      <Author>Sanghyun Ryu</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>21AUG2015</Date>
      <Description>Fix CalID due to the duplication</Description>
      <Author>Sanghyun Ryu</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Integer>
      <Value>5</Value>
      <MinValue>0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>255</MaxValue>
      <Units>seconds</Units>
      <Resolution>1.0</Resolution>
    </Integer>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="DTC_ENABLE_CRITERIA -Each fault detection algorithm may only be active (test running) in specific vehicle power modes or when a specific Virtual Network is active. All power modes/VN active states where the fault detection algorithm is active shall be specified for each DTC." Name="VN_ACTIVATION" Usage="LOW,GLOBALA,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_1BEY8EfTEeW-6Omy13RgGA</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>5/19/15</Date>
      <Description>Initial Release</Description>
      <Author>Sanghyun Ryu</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>21AUG2015</Date>
      <Description>Fix CalID due to the duplication</Description>
      <Author>Sanghyun Ryu</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Boolean>
      <Value>true</Value>
    </Boolean>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="DTC_ENABLE_CRITERIA - All DTC's should not set within 5 seconds of a under or over voltage condition." Name="RECOVERY_UNDER_OVER_VOLTAGE" Usage="LOW,GLOBALA,ENTRY_VCU">
